  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" Ishwar Chanda Sharma versus Devendra Kumar Sharma & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_5_2014_2061','2025INSC700'); ><font size='4'> <strong>ISHWAR CHANDA SHARMA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>DEVENDRA KUMAR SHARMA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 2014</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 700</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007672025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : BELA M. TRIVEDI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SATISH CHANDRA SHARMA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The issues raised in the present case relates to: (i) the eligibility of a receiver for Sri Giriraj Temple, Govardhan, Mathura; (ii) temples facing severe administrative issues of crowd management. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 &ndash; Or. XL, R.1 &ndash; &ndash; Mathura Region &ndash; Temples in grip of legal battles &ndash; Appointment of advocates as receivers &ndash; A stop-gap measure &ndash; The instant suit pending for 25 years &ndash; Temple trust running through receivers &ndash; No effort to conclude the civil proceedings &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 15-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 6855/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_5_2014_2061','2025INSC700','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><